  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "SOFTWARE DEVELOPER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles & Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li><p>Design, develop, test, and maintain software applications based on business and technical requirements.</p></li><li><p>Write clean, efficient, and well-documented code using appropriate programming languages and frameworks.</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with product managers, analysts, and other developers to deliver high-quality software solutions.</p></li><li><p>Perform debugging, troubleshooting, and performance optimization of applications.</p></li><li><p>Integrate software components, APIs, and third-party services.</p></li><li><p>Participate in system design, code reviews, and technical documentation.</p></li><li><p>Ensure applications meet security, scalability, and reliability standards.</p></li><li><p>Support deployment, maintenance, and enhancement of existing systems.</p></li></ul><p><strong>Requirements</strong></p><ul><li><p> Degree in Computer Science, Information Technology, or a related field.</p></li><li><p>Proven experience in software development and application support.</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of programming languages such as Java, Python, C#, JavaScript, or equivalent.</p></li><li><p>Experience with databases, data processing, and system integration.</p></li><li><p>Familiarity with software development life cycle (SDLC) and version control tools.</p></li><li><p>Strong problem-solving skills and attention to detail.</p></li><li><p>Ability to work independently and as part of a team.</p></li></ul>",
